Exam Structure (Quick Recap)

Part A – Foundation (75 mins)
- Numerical Ability
- Reasoning Ability
- Verbal Ability

Part B – Advanced (115 mins)
- Advanced Quant + Reasoning
- Advanced Coding (Mandatory for Digital/Prime)

1. Numerical Ability (Foundation) –  ~30–35% Weightage
 Topic                       Weightage   Priority 
 Percentages                | 8–10%     |  High  
 Ratio & Proportion         | 7–9%      |  High  
 Averages                   | 6–8%      |  High  
 Profit & Loss              | 6–8%      |  High  
 Simple & Compound Interest | 5–6%      |  High  
 Time & Work                | 5–6%      |  High  
 Time, Speed & Distance     | 5–6%      |  High  

 Topic                   Weightage 
 Mixtures & Alligations | 3–4%      
 Partnership            | 2–3%      
 Number System          | 3–4%      
 HCF & LCM              | 2–3%      
 Divisibility Rules     | 1–2%      

 Topic                     Weightage 
 Simplification           | 1–2%      
 Data Interpretation (DI) | 3–4%      

2. Reasoning Ability (Foundation) –  ~30% Weightage
High Weight Topics
 Topic                     Weightage   
 Number / Alphabet Series | 6–8%             
 Coding-Decoding          | 5–6%             
 Blood Relations          | 4–5%            
 Direction Sense          | 4–5%             
 Syllogisms               | 4–5%             
 Seating Arrangement      | 5–6%            

Medium Weight Topics
 Topic                   Weightage 
 Analogy                | 3–4%      
 Odd One Out            | 2–3%      
 Venn Diagrams          | 2–3%      
 Statement & Conclusion | 2–3%      

Low Weight Topics 
 Topic                Weightage 
 Clocks & Calendars | 1–2%      
 Puzzles (Complex)  | 2–3%      

3. Verbal Ability (Foundation) ~30–35% Weightage
High Weight Topics
 Topic                  Weightage 
 Reading Comprehension | 10–12%    
 Error Detection       | 6–8%      
 Fill in the Blanks    | 5–6%      
 Sentence Correction   | 4–5%     
 Para Jumbles          | 4–5%     

 Topic               | Weightage 
 Synonyms / Antonyms | 3–4%      
 Cloze Test          | 3–4%      
 Vocabulary          | 3–4%      

4. Advanced Quant + Reasoning –  Prime / Digital Level
High Weight Topics (Main Differentiator for Prime/Digital)
 Topic                                             Weightage 
 Advanced Percentages + Ratios                  | 10–12%    
 Advanced Time & Work                           | 8–10%     
 Advanced Speed, Time, Distance                 | 8–10%     
 Data Interpretation (Caselets, Tables, Graphs) | 10–12%    
 Logical Puzzles (Multi-step)                   | 10–12%    
 Probability & Permutation Combination          | 6–8%      
 Linear Equations & Inequalities                | 5–6%      

5. Advanced Coding (Most Important for Digital & Prime) –  ~40–50% Selection Impact
Core Coding Topics (90% of Coding Questions SPARK)
 Topic                                    Weightage 
 Arrays                                | 20%      
 Strings                               | 20%          
 Basic Recursion                       | 8%        
 Loops & Conditions                    | 10%     
 Functions                             | 7%       
 Searching (Linear, Binary)            | 8%        
 Sorting (Bubble, Selection, Built-in) | 7%        
 Pattern Problems                      | 5%        
 Time Complexity Basics                | 5%        

Bonus (If Time Permits – For Prime Aspirants)
 Topic                   
- Hashing (Basics)        
- Stack / Queue (Intro)   
- Simple DSA Logic        
- Input/Output Edge Cases 

Coding languages allowed: C / C++ / Java / Python
Aim: Solve 2 full coding problems in 90 mins

Smart Preparation Priority (What to Do First)
Must-Focus (80% Selection Impact)
- Percentages
- Ratios
- Averages
- Time & Work
- Series
- Coding-Decoding
- Reading Comprehension
- Arrays + Strings (Coding)

Important (15% Edge)
- DI
- Seating Arrangement
- Advanced Quant
- Recursion
- Binary Search

Optional (5%)
- Clocks
- Calendars
- Rare puzzles

TCS NQT 2026 Complete Syllabus & Weightage Ready
Focus Areas:
Quant: Percentages, Ratio, Averages, Time & Work
Reasoning: Series, Coding-Decoding, Seating
Verbal: RC, Grammar, Para Jumbles
Coding: Arrays, Strings, Sorting, Searching

For Digital/Prime → Advanced Coding is Mandatory
Follow a 30-day plan → Daily 2 coding problems + 1 mock
Consistency = Selection SPARK
